    "P < 0.05, permutation test, false discovery rate-corrected for multiple comparisons; n > 12. f, The 1-to-1 network takes as input an image sequence of the 10 most recent time frames (approximately 300 ms) of the visual experience of the male.",
    "Each image is a reconstruction of what the male fly observed based on male and female joint positions of that time frame (for example, c).",
    "The 1-to-1 network reliably predicts forward velocity (right, top), lateral velocity (right, bottom) and other behavioural variables (Extended Data Fig. 3) of the male fly.",
    "R 2 values are from held-out frames across control sessions.",
    "g,h, The 1-to-1 network also reliably predicts overall mean changes in behaviour across males with different silenced LC neuron types, such as forward velocity (g) and sine song (h)."
